(firstQuint)Are Two Antidepressants a Good Initial Treatment for Depression?.

 While antidepressant medications are often effective in relieving depressive symptoms, at least 60% of patients do not remit with the first agent tried.

 This pilot study will assess whether giving two standard medications simultaneously (i.

e.

, Escitalopram and Bupropion) is both tolerated and improves response while decreasing drop outs.

 This is a replication of a previous study.

